{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3503843,"name":"Wil Jankovic","username":"genpop","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/g/f0a364/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-02-06T06:25:40.297Z","cooked":"<p>Hello, Our team, 4537, have decided to use PathPlanner for our autonomous, and I, along with the rest of the programming team, and our mentors, have had some issue getting it to run spline/curve paths. Basic paths work(driving forward, driving back, strafing), but any time we introduce a curve, it always gets thrown off course in some way.</p>
<p>For the swerve drive code we are using <span class="abbreviation">YAGSL<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Yet Another Generic Swerve Library"></template></span>(Yet Another Generic Swerve Library), and we are using the NavX as our gyro.</p>
<p>Since other teams have been using PathPlanner, with swerve, and have succeeded, surely we are probably doing something wrong. Any help will be appreciated. <img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/images/emoji/google/smiling_face.png?v=12" title=":smiling_face:" class="emoji" alt=":smiling_face:" loading="lazy" width="20" height="20"></p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":5,"updated_at":"2025-02-06T06:25:40.297Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":24,"reads":69,"readers_count":68,"score":133.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":485408,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-having-issues-with-splines-curves","display_username":"Wil Jankovic","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":64752,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Software engineer, loves to learn"},"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-having-issues-with-splines-curves/485408/1","custom_user_title":"Software engineer, loves to learn","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3503911,"name":"Fletch","username":"Fletch1373","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/fletch1373/{size}/220073_2.png","created_at":"2025-02-06T13:04:02.998Z","cooked":"<p>Can you be more specific about the problem? Some questions to guide your response:</p>
<p>How far off?</p>
<p>Is it always by the same amount (e.g. always off by 10cm regardless of path)? Or same percentage (e.g. 1m path is off by 5cm, 5m path is off by 25cm, etc)</p>
<p>Can you share the actual path being taken?</p>
<p>Could you share a log file to show what odometry thinks it’s doing?  A video of what its actually doing might also be helpful, as would sharing your code (ideally as a link to github or similar).</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":5,"updated_at":"2025-02-06T13:04:02.998Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":55,"readers_count":54,"score":16.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":485408,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-having-issues-with-splines-curves","display_username":"Fletch","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":9105,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"3181/3015 Mentor | 213/1373 Alum | CSA/FTAA/Jack-of-all-Trades"},"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-having-issues-with-splines-curves/485408/2","custom_user_title":"3181/3015 Mentor | 213/1373 Alum | CSA/FTAA/Jack-of-all-Trades","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3506540,"name":"Wil Jankovic","username":"genpop","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/g/f0a364/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-02-09T05:29:15.025Z","cooked":"<p>The problem varies on the certain conditions. When I written a path to move forward and another path that strafes to the left. Like so,<br>
<img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/d/3/d3809f9ef2c5d2dd748125c267bea59474be3de4.gif" alt="2025-02-09 15-38-57" data-base62-sha1="ub2jTtwtZMIVtQeTl2cwZxwAfQg" width="690" height="388" class="animated"><br>
Instead, it moves forward, and does this,<br>
<img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/6/7/67b5d59a17da9f923a44993b5087bd4c2dc0789a.gif" alt="20250209_154349" data-base62-sha1="eNsKZ4HtXAMIIzfInKfl173M4oG" width="281" height="500" class="animated"></p>
<p>It is my first time using PathPlanner, and is the team’s first time using PathPlanner somewhat successfully. The angle is obviously off, and the gyro picks up on it. My AutoBuilder setup code does make sure it uses the gyro. Here is the code for setting up PathPlanner,</p>
<p>public void setupPathPlanner()<br>
{<br>
// Load the RobotConfig from the GUI settings. You should probably<br>
// store this in your Constants file<br>
RobotConfig config;<br>
try<br>
{<br>
config = RobotConfig.fromGUISettings();</p>
<pre><code>  final boolean enableFeedforward = true;
  // Configure AutoBuilder last
  AutoBuilder.configure(
          this::getPose2d,
          swerveDrive::resetOdometry,
          swerveDrive::getRobotVelocity,
          // ChassisSpeeds supplier. MUST BE ROBOT RELATIVE
          (speedsRobotRelative, moduleFeedForwards) -&gt; {
            if (enableFeedforward)
            {
              swerveDrive.drive(
                      speedsRobotRelative,
                      swerveDrive.kinematics.toSwerveModuleStates(speedsRobotRelative),
                      moduleFeedForwards.linearForces()
              );
            } else
            {
              swerveDrive.setChassisSpeeds(speedsRobotRelative);
            }
          },
          // Method that will drive the robot given ROBOT RELATIVE ChassisSpeeds. Also optionally outputs individual module feedforwards
          new PPHolonomicDriveController(
                  // PPHolonomicController is the built in path following controller for holonomic drive trains
                  new PIDConstants(0.037272, 0.0, 0.0),
                  // Translation PID constants
                  new PIDConstants(0.55, 0, 0.06)
                  // Rotation PID constants
          ),
          config,
          // The robot configuration
          () -&gt; {
            // Boolean supplier that controls when the path will be mirrored for the red alliance
            // This will flip the path being followed to the red side of the field.
            // THE ORIGIN WILL REMAIN ON THE BLUE SIDE

            var alliance = DriverStation.getAlliance();
            if (alliance.isPresent())
            {
              return alliance.get() == DriverStation.Alliance.Red;
            }
            return false;
          },
          this
          // Reference to this subsystem to set requirements
  );
</code></pre>
<p>And here is my custom method for getPose2d,</p>
<p>public Pose2d getPose2d(){<br>
return new Pose2d(swerveDrive.getPose().getX(), swerveDrive.getPose().getY(), getAHRSAngle());<br>
}</p>
<p>If you need me to elaborate further, I will try my best. Thank you for your help so far.</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":5,"updated_at":"2025-02-09T05:29:15.025Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":33,"readers_count":32,"score":16.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":485408,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-having-issues-with-splines-curves","display_username":"Wil Jankovic","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":9105,"username":"Fletch1373","name":"Fletch","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/fletch1373/{size}/220073_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":64752,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Software engineer, loves to learn"},"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-having-issues-with-splines-curves/485408/3","custom_user_title":"Software engineer, loves to learn","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3506546,"name":"Fletch","username":"Fletch1373","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/fletch1373/{size}/220073_2.png","created_at":"2025-02-09T05:49:37.642Z","cooked":"<p>Could you redo the test with the path going left first then forward? I’m curious if that changes the results in some way.</p>
<p>Theory: I suspect the weight balance is off on your chassis due to the battery being way at the edge (and no other massive components being mounted).  This would give the “rear” two modules better traction than the “front” two.  When moving forward, the left 2 and right 2 are evenly balanced.  When moving side to side, they’re not.  It’s not a clean explanation, because lower traction on the front wheels would equate to more wheel slip on those two and intuitively should manifest as a clockwise rotation rather than the counterclockwise your video showed.</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":5,"updated_at":"2025-02-09T05:49:37.642Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":28,"readers_count":27,"score":5.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":485408,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-having-issues-with-splines-curves","display_username":"Fletch","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":64752,"username":"genpop","name":"Wil Jankovic","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/g/f0a364/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":9105,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"3181/3015 Mentor | 213/1373 Alum | CSA/FTAA/Jack-of-all-Trades"},"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-having-issues-with-splines-curves/485408/4","custom_user_title":"3181/3015 Mentor | 213/1373 Alum | CSA/FTAA/Jack-of-all-Trades","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":fal